The food was disgusting. Well we had the Papusas which were normal/good. Nothing too exciting. But the batido de fresa was just frozen  strawberry margarita mix. Our entree was the fajita plate with chicken, beef and shrimp. It was awful. It just tasted like old disgusting meat that should have been thrown away. We literally could not chew the steak. It was just too tough and dry. The chicken was not as bad but it tasted old and dry too. And the shrimp was also bad! They were not shelled or cleaned. And they too tasted dry and old. We were so sad because there is a wonderful place across the street with really good meat for a really good price. The place is called Juanitas. Go there instead! They did not offer us a discount until we asked and then they just took off a percentage of the plate that we didn't eat. The manager never came out to apologize even though we were the only people there. We will never come here again!!
